## 9. Code Aesthetics & Vibe Principles

### 9.1 The Code Should Be Self-Documenting

Rather than:
```typescript
// Check if user logged in from unusual location
if (geoDistance(user.lastLocation, event.location) > THRESHOLD && 
    minutesSince(user.lastLogin) < 5) {
  // Suspicious
}
```

Write:
```typescript
if (user.hasUnusualLocationChange(event) && user.justLoggedIn()) {
  riskAssessment.escalate("Impossible Travel", { user, event })
}
```

**Principle**: Code narrates the business logic. A reader should understand what the code does without reading comments.

### 9.2 Pattern Consistency

All organs follow the same pattern:
1. Monitor (collect state)
2. Analyze (interpret state)
3. Plan (decide response)
4. Execute (apply response)

This means:
- Learning is fast (new developers understand the pattern immediately)
- Mistakes are harder (you can't deviate from the pattern)
- Code review is straightforward (you're checking if an organ follows its pattern)

